      <reaction compartment="compartment_70101" fast="false" id="reaction_1008220" metaid="metaid_135" name="Expression of globin genes under control of the beta globin control region" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The human beta-globin locus consists of five genes encoding the beta globin gene but also delta, gamma-A, gamma-G and epsilon globin. All of these genes are controlled by the beta globin locus control region.</p>
        </notes>
