      <reaction compartment="compartment_70101" fast="false" id="reaction_990489" metaid="metaid_153" name="Kinesin-13 is a dimer" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Kinesin-13 proteins are homodimeric with the kinesin motor in the middle of the amino acid sequence. They induce microtubule depolymerization by disassembling tubulin subunits from the polymer end (Desai et al. 1999).</p>
        </notes>
