      <reaction compartment="compartment_70101" fast="false" id="reaction_879459" metaid="metaid_160" name="F-actin capping protein is a heterodimer" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">F-actin-capping protein binds in a Ca2+-independent manner to the fast growing ends of actin filaments (barbed end) thereby blocking the exchange of subunits. Unlike other capping proteins (such as gelsolin and severin), they do not sever actin filaments.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
